2. **Commenting**: Added comments to clarify the purpose of various sections of the code, making it easier to understand the flow and logic.
3. **No Changes to Logic**: The existing logic for encoding characters and handling whitespace normalization was kept intact, as it seems to be functioning correctly. 

These modifications will improve the robustness of the `escape` function, ensuring it correctly escapes characters in various contexts while adhering to HTML encoding standards.

